<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Your OTP Code</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background-color: #f8f9fa;
      color: #212529;
      padding: 30px;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 500px;
      margin: auto;
      background: #ffffff;
      padding: 30px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    }
    .header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 25px;
    }
    .otp {
      font-size: 28px;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #007bff;
      text-align: center;
      margin: 20px 0;
      letter-spacing: 6px;
    }
    .message {
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 16px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .footer {
      font-size: 12px;
      text-align: center;
      color: #6c757d;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="header">
      <h2>Hello <%= username %>,</h2>
    </div>

    <p class="message">
      Here is your one-time password (OTP) to continue with your authentication.
    </p>

    <div class="otp"><%= otp %></div>

    <p class="message">
      This code is valid for only <strong><%= expiresIn %></strong> minutes. Do not share it with anyone.
    </p>

    <div class="footer">
      If you didn’t request this, please ignore this email.<br />
      — TravelTales Team
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
